msgctxt "seo_title"
msgid "Creative Futures Counterstructures | Mozilla Foundation"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "search_description"
msgid ""
"Creative Futures Counterstructures (CFC) is Mozilla Foundation’s 10-week cultural R&amp;D residency where creative technologists and communities come together to imagine, test, and build alternative"
" tech infrastructures."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "title"
msgid "Creative Futures: Counterstructures"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "hero_title"
msgid "Creative Futures: Counterstructures"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "hero_description"
msgid "A residency for creative technologists to prototype new cultural R&amp;D for AI."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "hero_image_alt_text"
msgid "A group of people standing and talking"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.d2a8543c-16c4-4962-97d6-d64b47dc1cbc.left_column.9e1cd6d9-3e11-450a-98da-d52d9cbd8054"
msgid "About the Program"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.d2a8543c-16c4-4962-97d6-d64b47dc1cbc.left_column.9e1cd6d9-3e11-450a-98da-d52d9cbd8054"
msgid ""
"Creative Futures: Counterstructures (CFC) is Mozilla Foundation’s 10-week cultural R&amp;D residency where creative technologists and communities come together to imagine, test, and build "
"alternative tech infrastructures."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.d2a8543c-16c4-4962-97d6-d64b47dc1cbc.left_column.9e1cd6d9-3e11-450a-98da-d52d9cbd8054"
msgid ""
"Through critical learning sessions, hands-on workshops, collaborative play, and a public exhibition, residents will design and prototype experimental counterstructures—cultural artifacts, "
"installations, and tools that question and reframe dominant tech systems."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.d2a8543c-16c4-4962-97d6-d64b47dc1cbc.left_column.c8c4f5d2-5bbe-42f9-a2a2-fd1ed25e4140"
msgid "Cultural R&amp;D"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.d2a8543c-16c4-4962-97d6-d64b47dc1cbc.left_column.c8c4f5d2-5bbe-42f9-a2a2-fd1ed25e4140"
msgid ""
"What if we asked creative communities what kind of tech they want—and then built it? Through our Imaginative Intelligences Assemblies, Mozilla Foundation and the Berggruen Institute convene "
"communities to articulate design principles for AI that put creativity at the center. Counterstructures residencies then turn those principles into tangible cultural artifacts, installations, and "
"tools."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.d2a8543c-16c4-4962-97d6-d64b47dc1cbc.left_column.c8c4f5d2-5bbe-42f9-a2a2-fd1ed25e4140"
msgid ""
"Each residency responds to a different Imaginative Intelligences: at tiat, residents prototyped in response to the eight design principles distilled with Hollywood artists and creatives, while at "
"Rhizome, residents took up principles of the commons articulated by our global futurist communities."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.d2a8543c-16c4-4962-97d6-d64b47dc1cbc.right_column.ce4c5709-9b89-45ca-a94d-71d44cd8247b.image.alt_text"
msgid "A yellow piece of paper on a table"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.e8532949-0ac5-48f9-aa29-20795886162c.title"
msgid "Past Residencies"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f47ae1e3-c14c-4a51-91ef-d1a129f6e761.left_column.6dc91f5b-59b8-410b-bcb1-fa05cc5aaabc"
msgid "tiat—San Francisco"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f47ae1e3-c14c-4a51-91ef-d1a129f6e761.left_column.6dc91f5b-59b8-410b-bcb1-fa05cc5aaabc"
msgid ""
"Our inaugural residency, hosted with tiat, asked creative technologists to prototype cultural infrastructure in response to the design principles of <a id=\"a1\">Hollywood's 8 Rules for AI</a>. The "
"resulting artifacts foregrounded human-in-the-loop creation, creative friction, transparency, lineage, slowness, and ecosystem stewardship."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f47ae1e3-c14c-4a51-91ef-d1a129f6e761.left_column.6dc91f5b-59b8-410b-bcb1-fa05cc5aaabc"
msgid ""
"Final works included a beating-heart installation that responds to human interaction, a microbial-powered AI hardware prototype, and an iterative performance where poetry evolved through audience "
"feedback. Across the residency, over 300 AI researchers, engineers, artists, and students joined the public programming and final exhibition."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f47ae1e3-c14c-4a51-91ef-d1a129f6e761.left_column.cc6ad198-ffd6-4dbd-b273-d65b5cdad2e8.label"
msgid "Read the Full Report"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f47ae1e3-c14c-4a51-91ef-d1a129f6e761.left_column.d52e0603-886e-4178-9b55-9ea3f0b913ea"
msgid "Rhizome—New York City"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f47ae1e3-c14c-4a51-91ef-d1a129f6e761.left_column.d52e0603-886e-4178-9b55-9ea3f0b913ea"
msgid ""
"Our Counterstructural Commons residency with Rhizome explored how artists can build alternatives to centralized technological systems. Responding to principles of the commons, the residency engaged "
"the tension between openness and extraction: how to advocate for an open commons while recognizing that openness has also left artists vulnerable to scraping and exploitation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f47ae1e3-c14c-4a51-91ef-d1a129f6e761.left_column.d52e0603-886e-4178-9b55-9ea3f0b913ea"
msgid ""
"Residents worked weekly from Rhizome's Lower Manhattan offices, developing counterstructures that took up guiding principles around community governance, technological agency, commoning, consent, "
"human-AI relations, and ecological accountability. Final projects were presented publicly at the New Museum."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.6d749a78-2b64-4b44-91e7-73fd2d896110.title"
msgid "Program Details"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.left_column.75e4cac8-8fb1-4fd9-b5b9-451433961d0f"
msgid "Who participates?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.left_column.75e4cac8-8fb1-4fd9-b5b9-451433961d0f"
msgid ""
"This residency is for creative technologists and multidisciplinary artists who use technology as a medium for cultural inquiry. Participants bring critical perspectives, research-driven practices, "
"and collaborative approaches to emerging tools. Experience with AI can be early-stage or advanced, but some proficiency with coding is required."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.left_column.4cbe18af-6e72-4c1f-9f6f-e48a35040da6"
msgid "What do residents receive?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.left_column.4cbe18af-6e72-4c1f-9f6f-e48a35040da6"
msgid "$2,500 (USD): $2,000 stipend + $500 materials budget"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.left_column.4cbe18af-6e72-4c1f-9f6f-e48a35040da6"
msgid "Weekly in-person work-sessions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.left_column.4cbe18af-6e72-4c1f-9f6f-e48a35040da6"
msgid "Guest lectures with practitioners across art, technology, and community design."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.left_column.4cbe18af-6e72-4c1f-9f6f-e48a35040da6"
msgid "Publication of final projects in a collective documentation report."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.right_column.cbba80e5-54b4-483c-9eb3-b7e096d68dda"
msgid "What do residents do?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.right_column.cbba80e5-54b4-483c-9eb3-b7e096d68dda"
msgid ""
"<b>Prototype an artifact:</b> Develop a counterstructure—an artifact, installation, system, artwork, or tool—for public exhibition. Projects should take up at least one of the guiding principles "
"specific to the residency call and articulated by the most recent Imaginative Intelligence assembly.You can find these principles in the application form."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.right_column.cbba80e5-54b4-483c-9eb3-b7e096d68dda"
msgid ""
"<b>Participate in programming:</b> Engage in listening, reading, sharing, workshops, and facilitated critique. Residents will test ideas with peers and community members, gaining access to audiences"
" and spaces to refine, iterate, and deepen the work."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.right_column.cbba80e5-54b4-483c-9eb3-b7e096d68dda"
msgid ""
"<b>Document and reflect:</b> Write a 750-word report capturing the project’s development, process, and insights. Documentation contributes to the Creative Futures Counterstructures Report and the "
"online archive."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.2a9d7e8b-f886-4a59-a16c-bbd5d246672c.right_column.cbba80e5-54b4-483c-9eb3-b7e096d68dda"
msgid "<b>Present:</b> Share your work with a public audience, as part of a culminating presentation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.f565291a-20b2-4752-a730-e3ac9468becc.title"
msgid "How to apply"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "body.9ab42b48-d752-4b36-8745-ca660e423b84"
msgid "We currently do not have any residencies running. Stay tuned for more updates about our open calls and exhibition dates."
msgstr ""
